  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.",
    "Add onion, garlic, celery, and carrots; sauté until vegetables soften, about 5 minutes.",
    "Stir in tomato paste and cook for 1 minute to caramelize.",
    "Deglaze the pot with 1 tbsp dry white wine, scraping up browned bits; let reduce for 1 minute.",
    "Add 4 cups of water, bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce heat and stir in basil, salt, and pepper; simmer for 10 minutes to meld flavors.",
    "Stir in lemon juice.",
    "Add ricotta cheese, whisk until smooth, and let the soup become fluffy; simmer 5 minutes.",
    "Adjust seasoning if needed; serve hot, garnished with extra fresh basil if desired."
